{"editorCode":";  \tA staircase between walls \n\n;Rosa wrote the procedure \"stair\"  in order to find the height and the width of 10 stairs that would cover the hypotenuse of a right triangle (its vertical sides are colored in blue).\n;When she executed the procedure as  \"stair 130 10 12\" she noticed that the stair did not cover the desired disctance. \n;After Rosa had adujsted the stair with the sliders, she claimed that she could rewrite the procedure with one parameter less. \n;Can you find out what Rosa meant and then modify the procedure accordingly?\n\n;Click the papyrus on the left to read\n;the activity instructions.\n;----------------------------------------\nTo stair :a :h :w\nsetpencolor [0 0 255]\nrt 90 fd :a lt 90 fd :a\nbk :a rt 90 bk :a lt 90\nsetpencolor [0 0 0]\nrepeat 10 [fd :h rt 90 fd :w lt 90]\nτέλος\ncs\nstair 130 10 12\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":" Instructions\n-----------\nα) Define the procedure \"stair\" and run it as stair 130 10 12  to see what the bird draws on the scene.\nWhat is the role of variables :a :h and :w in the procedure? \n\nTo define the procedure, select the lines from the word \"TO\" to the word \"END\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nTo run the procedure, click on the line \"stair 130 10 12 \" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nEnable the sliders tool by clicking on the bird trace in the scene. \n\nCan you adjust the slider with the help of the sliders, so that it covers the edges of both blue lines?\n\nb) Try to construct stairs that cover the height of the wall by changing the value of variable :a with the slider. \nCan you construct stairs for every value of :a? \nIf not for which values of :a can you create stairs and how many stairs do you create for each value? Why is this happening?\n\nc) Change the slider step of the variables :h and :w to 0.1. Do the answers to the previous question (b) change? Why?\n\nd) After Rosa constructed the stair she claimed that she could rewrite the procedure with one parameter less.  Η Ροζάνα αφού είδε τη σκάλα, είπε ότι μπορεί να ξαναφτιάξει τη διαδικασία με \nμία μεταβλητή λιγότερο.\nCan you find out what Rosa meant and then modify the procedure accordingly?\nDon't forget to redefine and re-execute the procedure to check your modification. \n\nTips\n-------------\n(d) The bird should fly the same horizontal and vertical distance. \nοντότητα είναι ίσες. ","sliders":{},"objects":[]}